  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research settings to predict hemolysis indices for centrifugal blood pumps operating under ventricular assist device conditions. The CFD hemolysis model targets the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry and has informed device design iterations at Model Risk Level 5. A 13-factor ASME V&V 40 credibility assessment was conducted; seven factors were evaluated and six were flagged as epistemic gaps. Despite gaps at MRL 5, the assessment team accepted the model for continued use given the supporting Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification and the conservative safety margins applied in downstream clinical research protocols. No structured Context of Use record is attached to this package; intended-use scope is conveyed only through this narrative.",
